      "solution": "import java.util.*\r\n\r\nfun main(args : Array<String>) {\r\n    val input = Scanner(System.`in`)\r\n    var text = input.nextLine()\r\n\r\n    val regex = \"(.)([-+]\\\\d+)\".toRegex()\r\n    val correctedText = regex.replace(text) { m -> \r\n        (m.groupValues[1].first().toInt() + m.groupValues[2].toInt()).toChar().toString() \r\n    }\r\n    println(correctedText)\r\n}",
      "statement": "The goal is to go through the text and make requested corrections. The correction instructions are in the form [[C+X]] or [[C-X]], where [[C]] is any letter (uppercase or lowercase) and [[X]] is a number {{1}} to {{25}}. The expected action is to shift letter [[C]] up or down by [[X]] letters (ASCII/ordinal/alphabet). Example: {{A+1}} becomes {{B}}, while {{z-25}} becomes {{a}}.\n\nIt's never needed to deal with rolling over the alphabet, e.g. {{A}} can only have positive shift values, while {{B}} can have the value {{-1}} or in the range of {{1}} to {{24}}.",
